ors of ordinary people in extraordinary times. Offering a window onto human relations and ethnic tensions in times of rampant violence, Jewish Childhood in Kraków is an effort both to understand the past and to reflect on the position of young people during humanitarian crises.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aChildren and warzPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aChildren and warzPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zPolandzKraków. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)zPolandzKraków. 0aJewish childrenzPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish childrenzPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish ghettoszPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish ghettoszPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszPolandzKrakówxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xChildrenzPolandzKraków. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xChildrenzPolandzKraków. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  ajew, jewish, judaism, antisemite, anti-semite, antisemitic, anti-semitic, holocaust, yiddish, cultural identity, identity, religion, ethnicity, zionist, zionism, israel, immigration, community, culture, jewish studies, wartime, German army, Germany, Jewish community, Poland, children, childhood, youth, Krakow, diaspora, child, concentration camp, survival, human rights, Childhood studies, humanitarian crisis, city life, adolescence, ghetto, jewish ghettos.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882297940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978822979423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978822979/original  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEB